Today's programme is
"Degawa Girls Gathering Special".

32
00:01:33,720 --> 00:01:34,920
Wasshoi!

33
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:35,920
"Morisanchu"

34
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,160
Hello.

35
00:01:37,240 --> 00:01:38,240
Hello.

36
00:01:38,320 --> 00:01:39,480
An Punch.

37
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:40,640
"Madame Dewi"

38
00:01:40,720 --> 00:01:42,120
Hello, everyone.

39
00:01:42,280 --> 00:01:43,680
All the girls are here.

40
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:45,800
It's the first gathering
after Yumeppe joined.

41
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:47,440
Yes, it's the first time.

42
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:50,520
I experienced many things
for the first time on this trip,

43
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:52,360
so I was excited the whole time.

44
00:01:52,440 --> 00:01:53,680
Were you?

45
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:57,440
I worried if you were okay,
it made me nervous.

46
00:01:57,520 --> 00:01:58,640
The old girls...

47
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,800
- Hey!
- Don't say that.

48
00:02:01,880 --> 00:02:03,080
We were nice.

49
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:05,680
She's just like Cinderella.

50
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:08,600
The step-mother and evil sisters.

51
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:09,800
That's not right!

52
00:02:09,920 --> 00:02:10,760
Not right?

53
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:14,520
I think the old girls
have been treating her well.

54
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:16,840
"Treat her well"?

55
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:18,360
Is that in a good sense?

56
00:02:18,440 --> 00:02:20,000
- We didn't bully her.
- The old girls...

57
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:22,280
"Degawa Girls Gathering Special"

58
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:24,840
Why did my body become like this?

59
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:27,360
Smile more cheerfully!

60
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:29,520
Stop it.

61
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:31,960
Come here!

62
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:36,040
"Enjoy the natural environment
in Iriomote Island!"

63
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:39,080
2,000 kilometres away from Tokyo,

64
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:42,360
the six people enjoy the natural
environment to the fullest.

65
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:46,480
Degawa Girls Gathering
in Iriomote Island.

66
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:50,480
Iriomote Island is Okinawa's
second largest island.

67
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,440
Most of it is a subtropical forest.

68
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:55,960
There are many
rare animals and plants,

69
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:58,920
so it's also called
Galapagos of the East.

70
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:00,440
We've come to

71
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:03,400
Iriomote!

72
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:05,000
So this time,

73
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:06,720
- Madame wanted to--
- Oh, come on!

74
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:08,360
come to Iriomote Island
no matter what.

75
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:10,840
That's right,
I've been longing to come here.

76
00:03:10,920 --> 00:03:12,640
- What's wrong with you?
- Bugs!

77
00:03:12,720 --> 00:03:14,800
There are awfully lots of bugs.

78
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:16,240
And this place is horrible.

79
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:17,960
- The opening!
- What happened?

80
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:21,760
That's nothing.
What are you doing, girls?

81
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:24,240
And what's surprising is,

82
00:03:24,320 --> 00:03:27,160
there are many bugs
flying around the four girls,

83
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:29,520
but none come near the two of us.

84
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:32,680
Maybe it's because we're poisonous?

85
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:34,560
At Hirai Farm,

86
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:37,680
Peach Pineapple,
Iriomote's speciality, is grown.

87
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:39,600
"Peach Pineapple"

88
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:40,640
It's sweet.

89
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,760
Wow, it's juicy.

90
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:45,800
It is small,
but it has high sugar content,

91
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:48,440
one of the expensive pineapples
costs 1,000 yen.

92
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:50,400
And recently,

93
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:52,520
Ms Kawakita just got married!

94
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,800
Congratulations!

95
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:57,800
So I'm glad that Ms Kawakita
comes here again.

96
00:03:57,880 --> 00:04:01,520
News online says, "Mayuko Kawakita
quits being a Degawa Girl."

97
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:02,720
Why?

98
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:03,960
Really?

99
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:07,120
They said, that is why
we have a new Degawa Girl.

100
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:09,120
- It's their imagination.
- How could you!

101
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:11,640
Now, Yumeppe, this is the first time
that you meet Madame,

102
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:13,720
introduce yourself
in the Fukushima dialect.

103
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:15,040
You're Fukushima?

104
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:16,280
Fukushima...

105
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:18,560
Hello, I am Yumeppe.

106
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:19,880
Nice to meet you.

107
00:04:19,960 --> 00:04:20,920
Adorable!

108
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:24,480
Madame, before Yumeppe
joined The Quest,

109
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:26,360
she had never even travelled
on a plane.

110
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:27,640
The girl is pure.

111
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:29,800
Everyone asked Yumeppe,

112
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:33,040
"You haven't been abroad?
You haven't been to Hawaii?"

113
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,640
Then Ms Kawakita said,

114
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:36,480
"Do you know what Hawaii is?"

115
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:39,360
No, no, no.

116
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:42,520
If she doesn't know, she can go
to tropical islands like this.

117
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:44,720
There isn't any adult
who doesn't know Hawaii!

118
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:46,920
I was going to tell her about it.

119
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,400
I know what Hawaii is.

120
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:50,480
She's angry.

121
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:53,400
Let's go, Degawa Girls Gathering.

122
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:57,040
First, we'll go river trekking
as Madame wishes.

123
00:04:57,960 --> 00:04:59,760
There are many rivers
in Iriomote Island,

124
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:01,680
and river trekking is popular.

125
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:05,720
Mr Nakagawa will be
our experienced guide.

126
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,160
- Are you our teacher this time?
- Yes.

127
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:08,120
Nice to meet you.

128
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:10,400
What time did you just say?

129
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:13,320
- This time.
- Oh, this time.

130
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:16,000
I thought I heard you say "society."

131
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:19,800
He'd be dressing wrong
in a ballroom.

132
00:05:19,880 --> 00:05:23,000
That's why I was wondering
what you were talking about.

133
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:24,560
You don't speak clearly.

134
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:25,680
Yes, I'm sorry.

135
00:05:26,080 --> 00:05:29,280
Actually, I have one good news
and one bad news.

136
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:31,480
- What?
- Which one do you want to know now?

137
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:33,320
- I want bad news first.
- Bad news first.

138
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:34,240
Are you serious?

139
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:36,680
- From bad news.
- You guys are on that side?

140
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,960
Along the way to halfway,

141
00:05:40,080 --> 00:05:42,080
there are quite a lot of bugs,

142
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:43,560
the worst case is leeches.

143
00:05:43,640 --> 00:05:44,840
- Oh, that.
- What?

144
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:45,840
Leeches?

145
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:49,320
They're all stuck here
before we realise.

146
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:51,800
Or they'll enter your nostrils.

147
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:54,920
"Ahahahahaha"

148
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:57,560
Or they'll go inside
your clothes here.

149
00:05:57,640 --> 00:05:59,520
- Go inside your top.
- Inside your mouth.

150
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,600
They'll go in from your back.

151
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:03,800
You're a hole and they'll go inside.

152
00:06:04,680 --> 00:06:07,080
You're a hole and they'll go inside.

153
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:09,800
And the good news is,

154
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:12,120
the Okugeta Waterfall
to which they'll go this time,

155
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:15,920
is an unusual place where even most
of the locals haven't been to.

156
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:18,320
Its beauty is guaranteed.

157
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:20,880
They go to the jungle
and towards the waterfall.

158
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:24,040
If you realise there's a leech
on your skin,

159
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:24,960
don't remove it by hand.

160
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:26,160
You'll bleed, right?

161
00:06:26,280 --> 00:06:28,680
Can we use that for our show?

162
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:29,840
Of course.

163
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:31,400
Then you're okay with it?

164
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:34,960
Really, she has grown stronger.

165
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:37,360
If there's a miracle
and I get stung by one.

166
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:38,920
It'll be a good story.

167
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:41,640
You talk like you want to be stung.

168
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:42,680
No.

169
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:45,120
They finally enter the jungle.

170
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:47,480
Wow, I love places like this.

171
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:49,760
- Someone said she loves it.
- Lovely!

172
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:51,240
Someone crazy is here.

173
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:53,080
Don't call her crazy.

174
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:56,840
Mr Nakagawa tells them to pay
attention to something important.

175
00:06:57,040 --> 00:07:00,840
For the next 10 minutes
in this forest,

176
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:03,080
you'll see many of this plant.

177
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:06,520
If you grab it and break the leaf,

178
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,640
- it oozes a white liquid.
- Okay.

179
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:11,560
If it sticks on mucous membranes,
like your lips or eyes,

180
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:13,600
you must be sent
to the hospital immediately.

181
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:15,320
What?

182
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:18,080
Also, there's a river
in front of them.

183
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:19,920
I have to get wet?

184
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:22,040
- I'll get wet right away?
- Be brave and get wet.

185
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,560
There'll be water
in the whole journey.

186
00:07:23,640 --> 00:07:25,520
Oh, is that what this trip is?

187
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:28,480
Mr Degawa, be careful.

188
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:30,800
Wow, I'm scared. It's...

189
00:07:30,880 --> 00:07:33,040
- Mr Degawa, you'll touch it!
- Watch out!

190
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:35,040
- Watch out!
- That was close.

191
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:37,080
- Oh, stop it!
- Mr Degawa!

192
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:38,520
The mic isn't waterproof.

193
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:39,520
Is it slippery?

194
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:41,040
No, you can do it.

195
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:42,920
- It's shallow.
- I didn't get wet at all.

196
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:45,480
Really? I'm soaking wet.

197
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:49,960
I've had enough! Hurry!

198
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:52,520
- Guys, don't fall!
- Wait a minute!

199
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:55,200
Wait, Yumeppe, don't fall!

200
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:57,880
Is that a cue?

201
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:01,080
"Hahahahaha"

202
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,280
She's laughing.

203
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:03,800
- Laughing.
- She's broken.

204
00:08:04,840 --> 00:08:06,200
Watch out.

205
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:09,600
While Degawa and the young girls
are screaming,

206
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:13,640
the 81-year-old Madame
is the best walker among them.

207
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:16,080
But I'm starting to feel good.

208
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:19,760
Then, the girls see the thing
they hate in front of them.

209
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:21,720
It startled me!

210
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:24,280
What the heck?

211
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:27,280
The microphone!

212
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:29,720
The microphone.

213
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:31,200
Microphone!

214
00:08:31,280 --> 00:08:34,240
Worry about Mayuko, not the mic!

215
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:37,240
She did that fantastic reaction,
don't worry about the mic first.

216
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,760
Exactly.

217
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:41,400
The mic is expensive.
It's 300,000 yen.

218
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:43,720
But I think the way I fell
was great.

219
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:47,080
It was worth 300,000 yen.

220
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:48,320
Let's go.

221
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:51,000
Please wait a second.

222
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:51,920
Madame.

223
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,760
- I'll leave you behind.
- We're a team.

224
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:58,160
They walk for another 30 minutes.

225
00:08:58,880 --> 00:08:59,720
Be careful.

226
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:03,120
Oh, here we are, here we are,
here we are.

227
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:05,440
They finally see a waterfall
in front of them.

228
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:08,920
But this isn't their destination.

229
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:11,600
We'll climb up there on the left.

230
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:13,120
What?

231
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:14,640
Can we go there?

232
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:16,920
That's right. They need to climb up

233
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,800
for 20 more minutes
to arrive at Okugeta Waterfall.

234
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:22,400
They've been here for an hour,

235
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:24,920
the 81-year-old isn't tired at all.

236
00:09:25,040 --> 00:09:25,880
Impressive!

237
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,000
I'm exhausted.

238
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:27,920
A good walker.

239
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,880
No wonder she wanted to do
river trekking.

240
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:33,200
And finally...

241
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,880
Wow, beautiful!

242
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:36,840
Amazing!

243
00:09:36,920 --> 00:09:38,400
Amazing!

244
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:40,600
I'm touched.

245
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:43,440
This is the stunning scenery
known only to a few,

246
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:45,040
Okugeta Waterfall.

247
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:47,240
It is about 15 metres tall.

248
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:51,240
Waterfall in steps like this
is rarely seen in Japan,

249
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:54,000
and if you look
at the opposite side...

250
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:56,680
Wow, beautiful!

251
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,320
I can see the sea.

252
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:01,120
It's the beautiful Sea of Iriomote.

253
00:10:02,160 --> 00:10:03,440
It's a spot with a stunning view,

254
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:06,560
where you can admire
a waterfall and the sea together.

255
00:10:08,640 --> 00:10:09,880
Wow, it's here!

256
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:12,680
The scenery is absolutely amazing.

257
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:15,440
- This is picturesque, Madame.
- Yeah.

258
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:16,920
Can our viewers feel it?

259
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:19,320
We spent a long time in the jungle,

260
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:21,280
then we see this
after we climbed up.

261
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:23,800
Ms Kawakita, look at the other side.

262
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:25,760
Wow, amazing!

263
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:27,320
It's awesome.

264
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:30,520
See? Everyone looks here first,
and goes, "Amazing!"

265
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:33,480
Akane, take that off,
turn around and look.

266
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:36,320
Wow, it's awesome!

267
00:10:36,560 --> 00:10:38,000
Look, Maria.

268
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:40,760
Isn't that amazing? Look behind you.

269
00:10:42,680 --> 00:10:44,000
Huh? What?

270
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:47,840
Each person feels differently.

271
00:10:47,920 --> 00:10:49,600
Come, Yumeppe.

272
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:51,000
- It's amazing, right?
- Yes!

273
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:53,800
But Yumeppe, look to the other side.

274
00:10:58,680 --> 00:11:01,520
Finally, they'll take a photo
for their calendar.

275
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:04,320
I hate getting soaking wet!

276
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:07,480
Stop complaining, just do it!

277
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:11,800
We'll take a photo of them six
standing on the waterfall steps.

278
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,000
Smile!

279
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:15,520
I'm smiling!

280
00:11:15,640 --> 00:11:17,080
Smile more cheerfully, guys!

281
00:11:17,160 --> 00:11:18,280
Smile!

282
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:22,920
"Wahaha"

283
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:26,320
It's a wonderful photo
with the six of them.

284
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:29,840
The flow of water
looks mysterious in it.

285
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,960
Tonight's hotel is...

286
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:35,280
Wow, amazing.

287
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:37,640
- Lovely.
- What happened?

288
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:40,800
This is Hoshino Resorts
Iriomote Hotel.

289
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:45,200
Iriomote Island aims to get
registered as a World Heritage,

290
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:47,640
so it's environmentally friendly.

291
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:50,240
They discontinued the use
of disposable amenities,

292
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:52,720
and provide rental
of water bottles.

293
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:55,840
Their hospitality
is environment-friendly.

294
00:11:56,280 --> 00:11:58,880
Open sesame.

295
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:03,240
They'll stay in this room.

296
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:04,840
Wow, it's big!

297
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:09,240
This is the Luxury Twin Room
with a day bed.

298
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:11,400
It costs 40,000 yen per night.

299
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,920
This is bigger than my home.

300
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:16,120
Really.

301
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:17,680
I think the best part is--

302
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:19,320
- That one, right?
- Yes, that.

303
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:20,240
I know.

304
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:22,560
Come, Yumeppe, lie down here.

305
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:24,560
Bask in the sun here.

306
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:26,760
Is it okay to bask in the sun here?

307
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:27,880
I'll lie down.

308
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:30,480
"Ahaha"

309
00:12:31,040 --> 00:12:32,360
She's adorable.

310
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:36,720
Okay, it's okay to lie down.
You can lie down.

311
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:38,600
- Do this?
- Yes.

312
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:43,400
The time this smile turns into
a fake one will come someday.

313
00:12:44,400 --> 00:12:45,480
Stop it!

314
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:46,760
It won't, right?

315
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:49,760
We have some bad news for them.

316
00:12:49,920 --> 00:12:52,920
Only Madame and Mr Degawa
can stay here today.

317
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:55,960
No.

318
00:12:56,040 --> 00:12:58,640
Degawa Girls aren't united enough,

319
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:02,680
so you'll stay at a campsite
to get to know each other better.

320
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:05,000
Hey.

321
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,160
Campsite?

322
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:09,160
I've been doing this
for seven, eight years and finally,

323
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:11,560
I can stay at hotels
like the ones in Dubai,

324
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:14,480
but I have to start from scratch
after Yumeppe joined?

325
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:15,840
What is this?

326
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:17,680
It's all Yumena's fault.

327
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:22,360
And this is the campsite.

328
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:23,280
What?

329
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,440
What's this?

330
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:26,440
This isn't for people to stay in.

331
00:13:28,160 --> 00:13:29,960
This is Mitrea Campsite.

332
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:33,560
- It costs 2,000 yen per night,
- It looks nicer now.

333
00:13:34,360 --> 00:13:37,360
The view from the campsite
is its selling point.

334
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:39,760
They check their rooms at once.

335
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:40,920
I see.

336
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:43,080
It's very simple.

337
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:44,600
You have one room each.

338
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:46,200
We can have one each?

339
00:13:46,280 --> 00:13:47,360
One each?

340
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:50,880
This isn't right, this isn't right!

341
00:13:50,960 --> 00:13:52,160
What do you think, Yumena?

342
00:13:52,240 --> 00:13:53,240
It looks a bit fun.

343
00:13:53,320 --> 00:13:55,240
That's not right.
Your perception isn't right.

344
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:57,680
Do you remember the hotel?

345
00:13:57,760 --> 00:14:00,120
We came here
after going to that hotel.

346
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:02,680
At the same time,
the elderly team...

347
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:04,160
- I'm jealous.
- Elderly team.

348
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:05,160
Delicious.

349
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:07,920
Wow, Madame, this is amazing!

350
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,800
What a feast!

351
00:14:10,280 --> 00:14:12,880
A lot of food ingredients
unique to Iriomote were used

352
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:14,520
to make the luxurious meal.

353
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:17,320
Chachacha...

354
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:19,960
Tatata...

355
00:14:20,640 --> 00:14:22,960
Madame is delighted.

356
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:25,120
- It's tender.
- Right?

357
00:14:25,280 --> 00:14:28,440
What do you think about
the new member Yumeppe?

358
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:29,720
Isn't it nice?

359
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:33,360
When a girl
who is totally different joins,

360
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:34,760
it's refreshing.

361
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:37,280
Do you think Akane has changed,
Madame?

362
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:38,480
She became a bit sophisticated.

363
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:42,760
Ms Kawakita got married, right?

364
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:43,680
What do you think?

365
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:46,320
They dated for seven years
and didn't get fed up,

366
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:48,800
so they must really love each other.

367
00:14:48,920 --> 00:14:51,440
Madame, can you love someone
for so long?

368
00:14:51,560 --> 00:14:54,920
The President told me
every single second

369
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:59,640
that he loved me, he loved me.

370
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:02,520
I was happy and blessed as a woman.

371
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:04,800
That's why I had no idea
he cheated on me.

372
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:05,760
Cheated.

373
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:07,920
He cheated on you!

374
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:10,600
At the same time, Degawa Girls...

375
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:12,640
Have you gotten used
to being a Degawa Girl?

376
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:16,480
Gradually, things like
the arrangements...

377
00:15:16,560 --> 00:15:17,560
"Arrangements."

378
00:15:18,560 --> 00:15:22,840
I'm impressed to see how you create
highlights for yourselves.

379
00:15:22,920 --> 00:15:24,400
Highlights!

380
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:26,280
Don't call it a highlight!

381
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:28,000
I do it naturally.

382
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:30,240
It's the first time you meet Madame,
right?

383
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:32,440
I was so worried that
Madame would not like me.

384
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:33,840
Why?

385
00:15:33,920 --> 00:15:37,600
I think she stares at people
and can sense something.

386
00:15:37,680 --> 00:15:41,240
In a way you haven't seen before,
Madame is going to...

387
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:42,840
shout.

388
00:15:42,920 --> 00:15:46,400
She enters the mode suddenly
when she snaps.

389
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:48,080
To make things worse,

390
00:15:48,160 --> 00:15:50,360
she'd tell you to do something,

391
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:53,480
then she'll go, "You!"

392
00:15:54,920 --> 00:15:56,600
She'll go, "You!"

393
00:15:57,880 --> 00:16:00,760
It really makes all of us tremble.

394
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:03,520
Then, the topic changes
to nice stories about Degawa.

395
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:08,680
Playing the rich lady character
makes me feel very inferior,

396
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:12,720
so Mr Degawa told me
to turn it into comedy.

397
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:14,480
He said that to me a lot,

398
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:17,160
then I stopped fearing anything.

399
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:18,640
Is it a good or a bad thing?

400
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:22,760
I was working as a model
when I started this,

401
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:25,720
I didn't like being teased at first.

402
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:29,320
But Mr Degawa told me
that people tease me out of love,

403
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:30,960
so I thought, he was right.

404
00:16:31,120 --> 00:16:34,040
I started to feel grateful
for being teased.

405
00:16:34,120 --> 00:16:37,440
He told me I can just be myself.

406
00:16:37,520 --> 00:16:38,840
It made me instantly realise that,

407
00:16:38,920 --> 00:16:42,480
and his words helped me a lot
after that.

408
00:16:42,560 --> 00:16:44,440
He said the same thing to everyone.

409
00:16:44,520 --> 00:16:45,720
- To sum up.
- In general.

410
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:46,720
It's copy and paste.

411
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:47,840
Copy and paste...

412
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:49,520
We realised.

413
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:54,600
I thought that he said what the girl
needed to hear,

414
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:56,120
but he said the same things to us.

415
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:57,840
Like saying that
would hit home anyway.

416
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:03,160
This is the end of day one.

417
00:17:04,120 --> 00:17:05,960
Madame, I'm impressed.

418
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:08,200
Didn't you get tired to go that far?

419
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:09,200
Not at all.

420
00:17:09,280 --> 00:17:11,600
I could've gone even further.

421
00:17:11,680 --> 00:17:14,480
- You're 81 years old.
- It's so impressive.

422
00:17:15,360 --> 00:17:18,040
Well, they just talked about it,

423
00:17:18,120 --> 00:17:21,520
Madame's voice is very loud
when she snaps.

424
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:24,840
When she actually snaps, it's...

425
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:26,280
"You!"

426
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:30,880
Yeah, when we're at the counter
in the airport, she really...

427
00:17:30,960 --> 00:17:32,760
- Really.
- No way.

428
00:17:32,840 --> 00:17:35,320
Just go and film outside
with her once.

429
00:17:35,920 --> 00:17:36,760
It's true.

430
00:17:36,840 --> 00:17:40,120
Even when we told Madame
she'd better not be so loud,

431
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:41,880
she goes, "It doesn't matter!"

432
00:17:42,040 --> 00:17:45,280
She doesn't care
when she is in that mode.

433
00:17:45,360 --> 00:17:46,960
That's what they say.
What do you think?

434
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:49,280
- Well, that happens.
- That happens?

435
00:17:51,040 --> 00:17:52,560
Day two of filming.

436
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:55,000
They go to a mangrove
with a stunning view.

437
00:17:55,520 --> 00:17:56,760
A mangrove is

438
00:17:56,840 --> 00:18:00,320
a general term for plants that grow
near the mouth of a river

439
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:01,960
where sea water
and river water mix.

440
00:18:02,440 --> 00:18:06,920
70 percent of mangroves in Japan
are here on Iriomote Island.

441
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:09,840
Indeed, there are a lot.

442
00:18:10,480 --> 00:18:11,840
It's all of that.

443
00:18:11,920 --> 00:18:13,520
It's so beautiful.

444
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,760
Is that called a mangrove?

445
00:18:15,840 --> 00:18:19,200
I knew it. I was thinking
why you were quiet.

446
00:18:19,280 --> 00:18:22,040
You've been observing.
You didn't say anything.

447
00:18:22,160 --> 00:18:24,040
Yumeppe, do you know
what a mangrove is?

448
00:18:24,120 --> 00:18:25,000
I don't.

449
00:18:25,080 --> 00:18:26,880
I only know Mitz Mangrove.

450
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:31,080
Oh, how cute.
There are many little ones.

451
00:18:31,600 --> 00:18:32,880
So cute.

452
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:34,920
Did you bring a camera, AYA?

453
00:18:35,880 --> 00:18:37,920
Take photos.

454
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:39,880
They do this every time.

455
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:41,720
Madame always gets angry and goes,

456
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:43,600
"AYA, take photos properly!"

457
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:45,760
"AYA! Take the photos here!"

458
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:47,240
When she said, "AYA!"

459
00:18:47,320 --> 00:18:50,320
AYA finally said,
"I'm here to do makeup for you!

460
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:52,160
I'm not your photographer!"

461
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:53,920
She fought back once.

462
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:55,640
"Makeup is a part of photography!"

463
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:57,040
What?

464
00:18:57,120 --> 00:18:59,200
Isn't photography
also doing makeup?

465
00:18:59,280 --> 00:19:00,360
Is it the opposite?

466
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:02,040
That makes AYA a photographer.

467
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:05,920
Why don't you carry a camera
with you?

468
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,400
- I'm carrying one.
- Yeah?

469
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:09,520
You startled me.

470
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:11,000
- I panicked.
- What?

471
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:12,280
I panicked.

472
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:13,880
- What's that?
- It startled me!

473
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:17,680
- I thought a crocodile appeared!
- I thought so too!

474
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:20,120
Gosh, cut it out!

475
00:19:21,920 --> 00:19:24,800
They'll go kayaking
as Madame wishes,

476
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,720
but as they're here...

477
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:28,560
We'll make it a race.

478
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:29,840
A race?

479
00:19:30,240 --> 00:19:31,400
The rule is simple.

480
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:34,640
Three teams of two
will have a kayak race.

481
00:19:35,240 --> 00:19:38,440
The last team will stand under
a waterfall as punishment.

482
00:19:39,040 --> 00:19:41,360
How will they decide the teams?

483
00:19:41,520 --> 00:19:43,600
The person who wins
a rock, paper, scissors game

484
00:19:43,760 --> 00:19:44,960
will choose a teammate.

485
00:19:45,040 --> 00:19:45,880
I have to win.

486
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:47,200
We'll choose.

487
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:48,320
I see.

488
00:19:48,440 --> 00:19:49,640
The first winner is...

489
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:52,080
Hotta.

490
00:19:52,320 --> 00:19:53,240
I'll choose Yumeppe.

491
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:56,040
Thank you!

492
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:57,960
Now, the fateful match.

493
00:19:58,120 --> 00:19:59,360
Who will win?

494
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:00,600
Rock, paper, scissors!

495
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:03,800
Kawakita wins.

496
00:20:05,360 --> 00:20:07,160
I won!

497
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:09,720
Winning rock, paper, scissors
means nothing.

498
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:12,040
It means something! I'll choose!

499
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:15,440
Who will she choose?
Degawa or Tani?

500
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:17,320
I'll choose Maria, of course!

501
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:21,400
- Hurray!
- We're going to win.

502
00:20:21,480 --> 00:20:23,360
Hurray!

503
00:20:24,240 --> 00:20:25,920
Thank goodness!

504
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:29,480
The good ones among us have to be
Yumeppe and Madame.

505
00:20:29,560 --> 00:20:32,880
- Why?
- Madame's arms are very strong.

506
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:35,840
Are you guys stupid?

507
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:37,840
He's only a weight.

508
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:39,920
Who are you calling a weight?

509
00:20:40,040 --> 00:20:41,000
Who is a weight?

510
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:43,080
What's your average age?

511
00:20:43,160 --> 00:20:44,920
"81 years old, 57 years old"

512
00:20:45,040 --> 00:20:47,680
Their average age is about 70.

513
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:51,040
Now, let's begin the kayak race.

514
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:53,360
The distance is 200 metres.

515
00:20:53,520 --> 00:20:56,760
The team that arrives at the goal
that is the pier, wins.

516
00:20:57,040 --> 00:20:58,160
Ready,

517
00:20:58,560 --> 00:20:59,520
start!

518
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:03,480
Right, left, right, left.

519
00:21:03,560 --> 00:21:05,680
They all started together.

520
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:08,960
But Team Kawakita
started to slow down.

521
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:10,080
You can do it.

522
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:13,480
Then, they suddenly changed
direction and went to the middle.

523
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:17,400
- You're in our way.
- You play dirty!

524
00:21:17,480 --> 00:21:18,480
Right, left.

525
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:21,920
This time,
Team Hotta goes near Degawa.

526
00:21:22,040 --> 00:21:24,200
Akane, don't come here!

527
00:21:24,360 --> 00:21:26,920
Why are you coming here?

528
00:21:29,120 --> 00:21:31,200
Right, left, right...

529
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:34,280
It becomes a triple dead heat.

530
00:21:36,080 --> 00:21:37,280
Ouch!

